We have that
\begin{align*}
\frac{\csc \theta}{\sin \theta} - \frac{\cot \theta}{\tan \theta} &= \frac{1/\sin \theta}{\sin \theta} - \frac{\cos \theta/\sin \theta}{\sin \theta/\cos \theta} \\
&= \frac{1}{\sin^2 \theta} - \frac{\cos^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta} \\
&= \frac{1 - \cos^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta} = \frac{\sin^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta} = \boxed{1}.
\end{align*}

Notice that the two fractions have the same denominator, so we can add them. Addition is commutative, so we can rearrange the terms to get  \begin{align*}
\frac{k-3}{2} +\frac{3k+1}{2}+3k+1 &=\frac{4k-2}{2}+3k+1 \\
&=2k-1+3k+1 \\
&=\boxed{5k}.\end{align*}

